After reviewing the code for secondary axes in ggplot2, I can see the issue with discrete breaks that have names. Currently, when a discrete scale has named breaks, those names aren't automatically used as labels for the secondary axis.

Here's my proposed edit:

```r
AxisSecondary <- ggproto("AxisSecondary", NULL,
  trans = NULL,
  axis = NULL,
  name = waiver(),
  breaks = waiver(),
  labels = waiver(),

  # This determines the quality of the remapping from the secondary axis and
  # back to the primary axis i.e. the exactness of the placement of the
  # breakpoints of the secondary axis.
  detail = 1000,

  empty = function(self) {
    is.null(self$trans)
  },

  # Inherit settings from the primary axis/scale
  init = function(self, scale) {
    if (self$empty()) {
      return()
    }
    transform <- self$trans
    if (!is.function(transform)) {
      cli::cli_abort("Transformation for secondary axes must be a function.")
    }
    if (is.derived(self$name) && !is.waiver(scale$name)) self$name <- scale$name
    if (is.derived(self$breaks)) self$breaks <- scale$breaks
    if (is.waiver(self$breaks)) {
      if (scale$is_discrete()) {
        self$breaks <- scale$get_breaks()
      } else {
        breaks <- scale$get_transformation()$breaks
        n_breaks <- scale$n.breaks
        if (!is.null(n_breaks) && "n" %in% fn_fmls_names(breaks)) {
          self$breaks <- function(x) breaks(x, n = n_breaks)
        } else {
          self$breaks <- breaks
        }
      }
    }
    if (is.derived(self$labels)) self$labels <- scale$labels
    # For discrete scales, if labels are still waiver and breaks have names, use those names
    if (is.waiver(self$labels) && scale$is_discrete() && !is.null(names(self$breaks)) && !is.function(self$breaks)) {
      self$labels <- names(self$breaks)
    }
    if (is.derived(self$guide)) self$guide <- scale$guide
  },

  # Rest of the code remains unchanged
  # ...
)
```

The key change is in the `init` method. After inheriting labels from the primary scale (if derived), I've added a check for discrete scales that looks for named breaks when labels are still set to `waiver()`. If named breaks are found and aren't a function, those names are used as labels automatically.

This preserves all existing functionality while adding support for named breaks in discrete scales to be properly displayed on secondary axes.

